# Internationalization Guidelines

## Supported Languages
This project supports 5 languages:
- English (en) - [messages/en.json](mdc:messages/en.json)
- German (de) - [messages/de.json](mdc:messages/de.json)  
- Spanish (es) - [messages/es.json](mdc:messages/es.json)
- French (fr) - [messages/fr.json](mdc:messages/fr.json)
- Polish (pl) - [messages/pl.json](mdc:messages/pl.json)

## Frontend Translation Patterns

### Using Translations in Components
```tsx
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';

const Component = () => {
  const t = useTranslations();
  
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{t('common.title')}</h1>
      <p>{t('form.step1.description')}</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

### Translation Key Structure
Use hierarchical keys with descriptive naming:
```json
{
  "common": {
    "title": "Title",
    "save": "Save",
    "cancel": "Cancel"
  },
  "form": {
    "step1": {
      "title": "First Step",
      "description": "Description for step 1"
    }
  }
}
```

### Locale Routing
- Middleware configuration: [middleware.ts](mdc:middleware.ts)
- Localized pages in [src/app/[locale]/](mdc:src/app/[locale]/)
- Use Next.js internationalization routing

## Backend Translation Support

### Email Templates
- Template files: [ddgro-nowy-backend/templates/emails/](mdc:ddgro-nowy-backend/templates/emails/)
- Follow naming pattern: `template_[locale].hbs`
- Use translation objects from [ddgro-nowy-backend/translations/](mdc:ddgro-nowy-backend/translations/)

### API Response Localization
```javascript
const translations = require('../translations');

router.post('/endpoint', (req, res) => {
  const locale = req.headers['accept-language'] || 'en';
  const t = translations[locale] || translations.en;
  
  res.json({
    success: true,
    message: t.success.operationCompleted
  });
});
```

## Best Practices
1. **Always use translation keys** - Never hardcode text strings
2. **Consistent key naming** - Use descriptive, hierarchical keys
3. **Fallback to English** - Ensure all keys exist in English as fallback
4. **Context-aware translations** - Group related translations logically
5. **Pluralization support** - Use appropriate plural forms for each language
